**Fixed.** The race condition is resolved:

- **Root cause**: The `if self.stock >= amount` check and `self.stock -= amount` decrement were separated by an `await asyncio.sleep(0.1)`. This allowed concurrent coroutines to all pass the check before any had decremented — classic time-of-check to time-of-use (TOCTOU) race.

- **Fix**: Added `asyncio.Lock` to make the entire check-and-decrement atomic. Only one coroutine can hold the lock at a time, ensuring no overselling.

- **Result**: 3 purchases succeeded (9 items), 2 were correctly rejected, final stock is **1** (never negative).
